	<li class="cat-item cat-item-53"><a href="http://www.bcgs.ca/?cat=53" title="Genealogy and Family History Events - British Columbia and Beyond

This list includes events, seminars, conferences and the like (not BCGS or other regular Meetings). Please forward information on upcoming events to the BCGS Editor editor@bcgs.ca and we will be pleased to include them in our on-line and printed publications. 

CANADA

British Columbia

June, Walking Tours with Maurice Guibord, Vancouver Heritage Foundation
June 25, 10 am, Hasting Park &amp; the PNE Fairgrounds; June 10, 10 am, Mountain View Cemetery

18 June 2016 - BC Highland Games. Look for the BCGS Tent. 
http://bchighlandgames.com/
Coquitlam, Percy Perry Stadium, 1299 Pinetree Way.

18-19 June 2016 - Scandinavian Midsummer, look for the BCGS in the Icelandic Room with the Scandinavian Genealogy Group. http://www.scandinavianmidsummerfestival.com/
Scandinavian Community Centre, 6540 Thomas St. Burnaby.

20 June 2016 = Organize, digitize, preserve your family history with Harley Cross of Share My Photographs, $10 dropin; refreshments. 10 am-noon.  http://ferrybuildinggallery.com/programs_events/arts_connection___networking_salon_for_artists
West Vancouver, Ferry Building Gallery, 1414 Argyle Ave.

July 17-23, 2016 - BCGS Free Library Week 
Open House, Sunday afternoon. 
The Library is open from 10-3 pm Monday to Saturday this week.

Mountain View Cemetery Tours

Lorraine Irving will be giving Mountain View Cemetery tours on the following dates: 

August 21st, 2016 - 11 a.m. - Accident victims - car, plane, boat, train, tram.
September 18th, 2016 - 2 p.m. - Murders in Early Vancouver -  Part 1
October 2nd, 2016 - 2 p.m. - Murders in Vancouver -  Part 2


July 24, August 14 and September 11, 2016 - Mountain View Cemetery Tours, Jewish Section. and Strathcona and Gastown tours. Jewish Museum and Archives, reserve ahead, $10:  http://jewishmuseum.ca/programs/historic-walking-tours/

23-25 September 2016 -  “Harvest Your Family Tree” Conference, Kelowna &amp; District Genealogical Society.
Kelowna, BC.  Details soon at  Kelowna and District Genealogical Society 

29 October 2016 - Brick Walls Seminar with talks and one-to-one sessions. Speakers: Brenda Smith, Peter Whitlock, M. Diane Rogers.
Cloverdale Public Library.  http://www.surreylibraries.ca/programs-services/4815.aspx


Alberta

July 29-31, 2016 - Note date change - Pack Your Research Toolbox, convention of the Society for German Genealogy in Eastern Europe (SGGEE)- research presentations on Germans who migrated through Poland, Volhynia, and surrounding areas.  Watch the website for details. Research Room at the convention.  
Radisson Hotel &amp; Conference Centre, Calgary Airport, 6620 36th ST NE, Calgary.



Nova Scotia

March 22, 2016 - Tracing your Irish and Scots-Irish Ancestors. Ulster Historical Foundation presentation, Genealogical Association of Nova Scotia
Delbert Hospitality Centre, Delbert,  




Manitoba



Ontario

2016 - Perth Military Settlement 200th Anniversary - many events scheduled. in Beckwith, Drummond/North Elmsley, Perth and Tay Valley.  See the Lanark County Tourism  website:  http://200thanniversary.lanarkcountytourism.com  or e-mail:  tourism@lanarkcounty.ca
And see the new maps and database availble at the anniversary website.
 

June 3-5, 2016 - Ontario Genealogical Society conference,  33 speakers! 
Toronto, Ontario.

September 9-11, 2016 -Family History Conference - Ireland and DNA in Genealogy. British Isles Family History Society of Greater Ottawa
Ben Franklin Place, 101 Centrepoint Dr. Ottawa. 

October 21-23, 2016  - Great Canadian Genealogy Summit Speakers: Kathryn Lake Hogan, Christine Woodcock, Mike Quakenbush, Ruth Blair and Louise St. Denis, Jennifer DeBruin and Lynn Palermo.
Courtyard Marriott,  Brampton, Ontario.


2017

June 16-18, 2017 - Ontario Genealogical Society conference, Our Canada - Your Family: Building a Nation. The OGS Ottawa Branch is sponsoring. 
Ottawa, Algonquin College. http://ogsottawa.on.ca/conference-2017/



Quebec

September 30-2 October 2016 -  &quot;Mouvements collectifs, destinées familiales: migrations canadiennes-françaises au Canada 1830-1930&quot;, FQSG/SGQ Congrés 2016.
Hôtel Québec, 3115, avenue des Hôtels, Québec.

Saskatchewan

April 15-17, 2016 - Diving Into the Genealogy Pool, Saskatchewan Genealogical Society conference. Speakers include Dale Eisler, Tammy Tipler-Priolo, Alan B. Anderson, John Althouse, Glenn Schwartz, Chris Krismer, Catherine Holmes.
Ramada Plaza, Regina.

FRANCE



UNITED KINGDOM OF GREAT BRITAIN AND NORTHERN IRELAND

